## 1. High-Level System Architecture
```
// High-Level System Architecture
title K-pop Recommendation Service - System Overview

Clients [icon: users, color: blue]
FastAPI Service [icon: server, color: orange]
LightFM Model [icon: brain, color: red]
PostgreSQL [icon: database, color: blue]
Cron Training [icon: clock, color: green]

Clients > FastAPI Service: API Requests
FastAPI Service > LightFM Model: Get Recommendations
FastAPI Service > PostgreSQL: Query Data
Cron Training > PostgreSQL: Load Training Data
Cron Training > LightFM Model: Update Model (Every 5 min)
```

## 2. Request Flow
```
// Recommendation Request Flow
title How Recommendations Work

Client [icon: user, color: blue]
API [icon: server, color: orange]
ML Engine [icon: brain, color: red]
Database [icon: database, color: blue]

Client > API: Request recommendations
API > ML Engine: Get scores for user
ML Engine > Database: Fetch features
Database > ML Engine: User & post data
ML Engine > API: Top recommendations
API > Client: 20 posts (paginated)
```

## 3. Training Pipeline
```
// Automated Training
title Automated Model Training (Every 5 Minutes)

Database [icon: database, color: blue]
Training Process [icon: gear, color: orange]
ML Model [icon: brain, color: red]
API Service [icon: server, color: green]

Database > Training Process: Load data\n(Users, Posts, Interactions)
Training Process > Training Process: Build features\nTrain LightFM (~45s)
Training Process > ML Model: Save new model
ML Model > API Service: Hot reload\n(Zero downtime)
```

